      <hedline>
        <hl1>Hearing Is Scheduled On Rising Fuel Costs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Westchester County Exec Andrew Spano schedules public hearing on rising cost of fuel; drawing (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>County Executive Andrew J. Spano will hold a public hearing Oct. 23 on the rising cost of fuel.</p>
        <p>''We are in a crisis situation,'' Mr. Spano said. ''Rates are soaring and I am concerned that many of our residents, especially those on fixed incomes, will have to choose between fuel and food this winter. I want to do everything I can to lower heating costs and electric rates. And that's what this hearing is all about.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>County Executive Andrew J. Spano will hold a public hearing Oct. 23 on the rising cost of fuel.</p>
        <p>''We are in a crisis situation,'' Mr. Spano said. ''Rates are soaring and I am concerned that many of our residents, especially those on fixed incomes, will have to choose between fuel and food this winter. I want to do everything I can to lower heating costs and electric rates. And that's what this hearing is all about.''</p>
        <p>The hearing will be held at 10 a.m. at the Westchester County Center in White Plains. Mr. Spano said he hopes to develop proposals to forward to state and federal officials.  IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
